    public interface ValueHolder
    Base class of specialized None and Some holders. All implementations of ValueHolder must provide specialized getValue methods. getValue methods may throw UnsupportedOperationException when called on None holders. A check should be made through hasSome() to ensure that the ValueHolder has value. Whenever hasSome() returns true, getValue must not throw any exception.
